.TH B64 "1" "October 2018" "dotfiles" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
b64 \- b64
.SH DESCRIPTION
Extends base64 with the ability to handle URLs and input strings as an argument.
.PP
By default outputs the encoded string on a single line, primed for data\-uri
usage.
.SS "Usage:"
.IP
$ b64 [options] [file|input|url] [resource] [base64\-options]
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print this message
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version number
.SS "Commands:"
.IP
$ b64 file [path]
Encodes or decodes a file.
.IP
\f(CW$ b64 input [value]\fR
.IP
Encodes or decodes an input value.
.IP
\f(CW$ b64 url [url]\fR
.IP
Encodes or decodes an URL's response body.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
\f(CW$ b64 file ~/.gitconfig\fR
.IP
\f(CW> SGVsbG8gV29ybGQhCg==\fR
.IP
\f(CW$ b64 input "Hello world!"\fR
.IP
\f(CW> SGVsbG8gV29ybGQh\fR
.IP
\f(CW$ b64 input "SGVsbG8gV29ybGQh" --decode\fR
.IP
\f(CW> "Hello World!"\fR
.IP
\f(CW$ b64 url https://localhost/image.png\fR
.IP
\f(CW> SGVsbG8gV29ybGQh\fR
.IP
\f(CW$ b64 https://localhost/with/protocol/scheme.png\fR
.IP
\f(CW> SGVsbG8gV29ybGQh\fR
.IP
\f(CW$ b64 url\fR
.IP
? URL:
.IP
\f(CW$ b64 input\fR
.IP
? Input:
.IP
\f(CW$ echo "Hello World!" > "filename.txt"\fR
.br
\f(CW$ b64 filename.txt\fR
.IP
\f(CW> SGVsbG8gV29ybGQhCg==\fR
.IP
\f(CW$ echo "Hello World!" | b64\fR
.IP
\f(CW> SGVsbG8gV29ybGQhCg==\fR
